clnpForwarding.name: clnpForwarding
clnpForwarding.description: The indication of whether this entity is active as an intermediate or end system. Only intermediate systems will forward PDUs onward that are not addressed to them.

clnpDefaultLifeTime.name: clnpDefaultLifeTime
clnpDefaultLifeTime.description: The default value inserted into the Lifetime field of the CLNP PDU header of PDUs sourced by this entity.

clnpInReceives.name: clnpInReceives
clnpInReceives.description: The total number of input PDUs received from all connected network interfaces running CLNP, including errors.

clnpInHdrErrors.name: clnpInHdrErrors
clnpInHdrErrors.description: The number of input PDUs discarded due to errors in the CLNP header, including bad checksums, version mismatch, lifetime exceeded, errors discovered in processing options, etc.

clnpInAddrErrors.name: clnpInAddrErrors
clnpInAddrErrors.description: The number of input PDUs discarded because the NSAP address in the CLNP header's destination field was not a valid NSAP to be received at this entity. This count includes addresses not understood. For end systems, this is a count of PDUs which arrived with a destination NSAP which was not local.

clnpForwPDUs.name: clnpForwPDUs
clnpForwPDUs.description: The number of input PDUs for which this entity was not the final destination and which an attempt was made to forward them onward.

clnpInUnknownNLPs.name: clnpInUnknownNLPs
clnpInUnknownNLPs.description: The number of locally-addressed PDUs successfully received but discarded because the network layer protocol was unknown or unsupported (e.g., not CLNP or ES-IS).

clnpInUnknownULPs.name: clnpInUnknownULPs
clnpInUnknownULPs.description: The number of locally-addressed PDUs successfully received but discarded because the upper layer protocol was unknown or unsupported (e.g., not TP4).

clnpInDiscards.name: clnpInDiscards
clnpInDiscards.description: The number of input CLNP PDUs for which no problems were encountered to prevent their continued processing, but were discarded (e.g., for lack of buffer space). Note that this counter does not include any PDUs discarded while awaiting re-assembly.

clnpInDelivers.name: clnpInDelivers
clnpInDelivers.description: The total number of input PDUs successfully delivered to the CLNS transport user.

clnpOutRequests.name: clnpOutRequests
clnpOutRequests.description: The total number of CLNP PDUs which local CLNS user protocols supplied to CLNP for transmission requests. This counter does not include any PDUs counted in clnpForwPDUs.

clnpOutDiscards.name: clnpOutDiscards
clnpOutDiscards.description: The number of output CLNP PDUs for which no other problem was encountered to prevent their transmission but were discarded (e.g., for lack of buffer space). Note this counter includes PDUs counted in clnpForwPDUs.

clnpOutNoRoutes.name: clnpOutNoRoutes
clnpOutNoRoutes.description: The number of CLNP PDUs discarded because no route could be found to transmit them to their destination. This counter includes any PDUs counted in clnpForwPDUs.

clnpReasmTimeout.name: clnpReasmTimeout
clnpReasmTimeout.description: The maximum number of seconds which received segments are held while they are awaiting reassembly at this entity.

clnpReasmReqds.name: clnpReasmReqds
clnpReasmReqds.description: The number of CLNP segments received which needed to be reassembled at this entity.

clnpReasmOKs.name: clnpReasmOKs
clnpReasmOKs.description: The number of CLNP PDUs successfully re-assembled at this entity.

clnpReasmFails.name: clnpReasmFails
clnpReasmFails.description: The number of failures detected by the CLNP reassembly algorithm (for any reason: timed out, buffer size, etc).

clnpSegOKs.name: clnpSegOKs
clnpSegOKs.description: The number of CLNP PDUs that have been successfully segmented at this entity.

clnpSegFails.name: clnpSegFails
clnpSegFails.description: The number of CLNP PDUs that have been discarded because they needed to be fragmented at this entity but could not.

clnpSegCreates.name: clnpSegCreates
clnpSegCreates.description: The number of CLNP PDU segments that have been generated as a result of segmentation at this entity.

clnpInOpts.name: clnpInOpts
clnpInOpts.description: The number of CLNP PDU segments that have been input with options at this entity.

clnpOutOpts.name: clnpOutOpts
clnpOutOpts.description: The number of CLNP PDU segments that have been generated with options by this entity.

clnpRoutingDiscards.name: clnpRoutingDiscards
clnpRoutingDiscards.description: The number of routing entries which were chosen to be discarded even though they are valid. One possible reason for discarding such an entry could be to free-up buffer space for other routing entries.

clnpAddrTable.name: clnpAddrTable
clnpAddrTable.description: The table of addressing information relevant to this entity's CLNP addresses.

clnpAddrEntry.name: clnpAddrEntry
clnpAddrEntry.description: The addressing information for one of this entity's CLNP addresses.

clnpAdEntAddr.name: clnpAdEntAddr
clnpAdEntAddr.description: The CLNP address to which this entry's addressing information pertains.

clnpAdEntIfIndex.name: clnpAdEntIfIndex
clnpAdEntIfIndex.description: The index value which uniquely identifies the interface to which this entry is applicable. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of ifIndex.

clnpAdEntReasmMaxSize.name: clnpAdEntReasmMaxSize
clnpAdEntReasmMaxSize.description: The size of the largest CLNP PDU which this entity can re-assemble from incoming CLNP segmented PDUs received on this interface.

clnpRouteEntry.name: clnpRouteEntry
clnpRouteEntry.description: A route to a particular destination.

clnpRouteDest.name: clnpRouteDest
clnpRouteDest.description: The destination CLNP address of this route.

clnpRouteIfIndex.name: clnpRouteIfIndex
clnpRouteIfIndex.description: The index value which uniquely identifies the local interface through which the next hop of this route should be reached. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same as identified by the same value of ifIndex.

clnpRouteMetric1.name: clnpRouteMetric1
clnpRouteMetric1.description: The primary routing metric for this route. The semantics of this metric are determined by the routing-protocol specified in the route's clnpRouteProto value. If this metric is not used, its value should be set to -1.

clnpRouteMetric2.name: clnpRouteMetric2
clnpRouteMetric2.description: An alternate routing metric for this route. The semantics of this metric are determined by the routing-protocol specified in the route's clnpRouteProto value. If this metric is not used, its value should be set to -1.

clnpRouteMetric3.name: clnpRouteMetric3
clnpRouteMetric3.description: An alternate routing metric for this route. The semantics of this metric are determined by the routing-protocol specified in the route's clnpRouteProto value. If this metric is not used, its value should be set to -1.

clnpRouteMetric4.name: clnpRouteMetric4
clnpRouteMetric4.description: An alternate routing metric for this route. The semantics of this metric are determined by the routing-protocol specified in the route's clnpRouteProto value. If this metric is not used, its value should be set to -1.

clnpRouteNextHop.name: clnpRouteNextHop
clnpRouteNextHop.description: The CLNP address of the next hop of this route.

clnpRouteType.name: clnpRouteType
clnpRouteType.description: The type of route. Setting this object to the value invalid(2) has the effect of invaliding the corresponding entry in the clnpRoutingTable. That is, it effectively dissasociates the destination identified with said entry from the route identified with said entry. It is an implementation-specific matter as to whether the agent removes an invalidated entry from the table. Accordingly, management stations must be prepared to receive tabular information from agents that corresponds to entries not currently in use. Proper interpretation of such entries requires examination of the relevant clnpRouteType object.

clnpRouteProto.name: clnpRouteProto
clnpRouteProto.description: The routing mechanism via which this route was learned. Inclusion of values for gateway routing protocols is not intended to imply that hosts should support those protocols.

clnpRouteAge.name: clnpRouteAge
clnpRouteAge.description: The number of seconds since this route was last updated or otherwise determined to be correct. Note that no semantics of `too old' can be implied except through knowledge of the routing protocol by which the route was learned.

clnpRouteMetric5.name: clnpRouteMetric5
clnpRouteMetric5.description: An alternate routing metric for this route. The semantics of this metric are determined by the routing-protocol specified in the route's clnpRouteProto value. If this metric is not used, its value should be set to -1.

clnpRouteInfo.name: clnpRouteInfo
clnpRouteInfo.description: A reference to MIB definitions specific to the particular routing protocol which is responsible for this route, as determined by the value specified in the route's clnpRouteProto value. If this information is not present, its value should be set to the OBJECT IDENTIFIER { 0 0 }, which is a syntatically valid object identifier, and any conformant implementation of ASN.1 and BER must be able to generate and recognize this value.

clnpNetToMediaTable.name: clnpNetToMediaTable
clnpNetToMediaTable.description: The CLNP Address Translation table used for mapping from CLNP addresses to physical addresses.

clnpNetToMediaEntry.name: clnpNetToMediaEntry
clnpNetToMediaEntry.description: Each entry contains one CLNP address to `physical' address equivalence.

clnpNetToMediaIfIndex.name: clnpNetToMediaIfIndex
clnpNetToMediaIfIndex.description: The interface on which this entry's equivalence is effective. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of ifIndex.

clnpNetToMediaNetAddress.name: clnpNetToMediaNetAddress
clnpNetToMediaNetAddress.description: The CLNP address corresponding to the media- dependent `physical' address.

clnpNetToMediaType.name: clnpNetToMediaType
clnpNetToMediaType.description: The type of mapping. Setting this object to the value invalid(2) has the effect of invalidating the corresponding entry in the clnpNetToMediaTable. That is, it effectively dissassociates the interface identified with said entry from the mapping identified with said entry. It is an implementation-specific matter as to whether the agent removes an invalidated entry from the table. Accordingly, management stations must be prepared to receive tabular information from agents that corresponds to entries not currently in use. Proper interpretation of such entries requires examination of the relevant clnpNetToMediaType object.

clnpNetToMediaAge.name: clnpNetToMediaAge
clnpNetToMediaAge.description: The number of seconds since this entry was last updated or otherwise determined to be correct. Note that no semantics of `too old' can be implied except through knowledge of the type of entry.

clnpNetToMediaHoldTime.name: clnpNetToMediaHoldTime
clnpNetToMediaHoldTime.description: The time in seconds this entry will be valid. Static entries should always report this field as -1.

clnpMediaToNetTable.name: clnpMediaToNetTable
clnpMediaToNetTable.description: The CLNP Address Translation table used for mapping from physical addresses to CLNP addresses.

clnpMediaToNetEntry.name: clnpMediaToNetEntry
clnpMediaToNetEntry.description: Each entry contains on ClnpAddress to `physical' address equivalence.

clnpMediaToNetIfIndex.name: clnpMediaToNetIfIndex
clnpMediaToNetIfIndex.description: The interface on which this entry's equivalence is effective. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of ifIndex.

clnpMediaToNetAddress.name: clnpMediaToNetAddress
clnpMediaToNetAddress.description: The ClnpAddress corresponding to the media- dependent `physical' address.

clnpMediaToNetType.name: clnpMediaToNetType
clnpMediaToNetType.description: The type of mapping. Setting this object to the value invalid(2) has the effect of invalidating the corresponding entry in the clnpMediaToNetTable. That is, it effectively dissassociates the interface identified with said entry from the mapping identified with said entry. It is an implementation-specific matter as to whether the agent removes an invalidated entry from the table. Accordingly, management stations must be prepared to receive tabular information from agents that corresponds to entries not currently in use. Proper interpretation of such entries requires examination of the relevant clnpMediaToNetType object.

clnpMediaToNetAge.name: clnpMediaToNetAge
clnpMediaToNetAge.description: The number of seconds since this entry was last updated or otherwise determined to be correct. Note that no semantics of `too old' can be implied except through knowledge of the type of entry.

clnpMediaToNetHoldTime.name: clnpMediaToNetHoldTime
clnpMediaToNetHoldTime.description: The time in seconds this entry will be valid. Static entries should always report this field as -1.
